<question-stem>
<para> What does the professor say is surprising about medium-sized asteroids?<mediaExhibit
frameType="mp3" mediaRef="toeflPrac10227.mp3"/></para>
</question-stem>
<answer-choice-set>
<answer-choice> They are thought to hit Earth every 500,000 years.</answer-choice>
<answer-choice correct="yes"> More damage would be caused by atmospheric pollution
than by their actual impact.</answer-choice>
<answer-choice> There are several hundred of them discovered near Earth every
year.</answer-choice>
<answer-choice> More have hit Earth in the past million years than at any
other time in Earth's history.</answer-choice>
</answer-choice-set>
<explanation interaction="true">
<para> (B) is correct because the professor states that the surprising thing
is that the most damage is not caused by the impact, but (is caused by) atmospheric
poisoning. This is the only point of reference he makes to <emphasis emphasis-type="italic"> surprisingly, </emphasis>so
(A), (C) and (D) are incorrect.</para>
</explanation>
